climbs.name: Whiskey Blend (aka Slob)
climbs.fa: Duncan Murray, Greg M, Clark O, Zack G, 9/2010

content.description: The route climbs past bolts trending left to a large right trending flake. Pull over the flake and keep going up to the chains.
content.location: On the east facing side of the crag. Look for the bolt just below the undercling flake.

content.description:
Start on left side of arch and follow the crack feature through 4 bolts. After 4th bolt, cross over a ledge and up toward anchor on face above. Crux is pulling over/around the roof. Starts near Chossylvania, but climbs out of alcove almost immediately.

Beware of loose rock!! Route should clean up with more traffic.
content.protection: Protects with quickdraws (6 bolts) to bolted anchor with chains.
content.location: Starts near Chossylvania, but climbs out of alcove almost immediately. Refer to beta photo on Cannibus Crew Wall page.

content.description: Nearly the same climb as the far right warm-up route, both more difficult than they look. Shares anchors with the right route. You would not want to have a climber on both routes at the same time.
content.protection: 4/5 bolts? shares anchors with route to right
content.location: Second from the right, very closely bolted with the far right route. Almost the same route. Left side of a wide but shallow runnel or chimney looking feature, which is just left of the larger cave.

climbs.name: Lucky 13
climbs.fa: Darren Edmunds, Jimmy F, Greg M, 9/2012

content.description: Follows three bolts up steep sidepulls and joins up with the upper section of Whiskey Blend after the undercling flake.
content.location: Just a few feet left of Slob on some crisp sidepulls.

climbs.name: Jugs (aka Slob's Warm-up)
climbs.fa: Greg M, Luke and Stacy D, Marla Baily, 7/2011

content.description: The crux for this moderate climb is checking the barndoor as you transition left.
content.protection: 4 bolts and chains, shares anchor with another route to the left.
content.location: Rightmost bolted route.  Chains are on the right at the top.

content.description: Also known as Blob's Warm-up, you will find climbing that can be harder than it looks in the middle portion.
content.location: Toward the right side of the main face. 3rd bolted route from the right.

content.description:
"Newer" route not described in Utah's West Desert guidebook by James Garrett (2011)

Climb the face on awkward features to reach a series of undercling crack features below the roof. Clip bolt 4 below the roof and solve the puzzling roof to gain the final bolt on the face above.

Beware of loose rock!! Route should clean up with more traffic.
content.protection: Protects with quickdraws (6 bolts) to bolted anchor with chains.
content.location: Refer to beta photo on Cannibus Crews Wall page.

climbs.name: Cannibas Crew (aka Bobbin Heads)
climbs.fa: Doug M, Greg M, Jimmy F, 9/2010

content.description:
Great arete climb with some pumpy moves near the top as you climb over the bulge. Steep jug haul which climbs the face just to the right of the large arch. Follows arete just to the right of Cannabis Corner. Named

Bobbin Heads

in another book.
content.protection: Protects with quickdraws (5 bolts). Shares anchors with route at left.

climbs.name: Cannibas Corner (aka Jumbled Spreadsheets Ahead)
climbs.fa: Zack G, Tina, Clark O, Greg M, Duncan Murray, 9/2010

content.description:
Stem up to roof using crack features and good ledges. After crossing right at roof, find crux as you exit the arch to anchors. Crux is clipping with one hand in the jam and then pulling off of it. Exciting Climb! Known as

Jumbled Spreadsheets

in another book
content.protection: Climb protects with quickdraws (5 bolts). Shares bolted anchors with route at right.
content.location: Climbs the dihedral and crack features on the right hand side of the big overhanging arch. Starts on the far right side of shallow alcove and roughly follows dihedral. See beta photo on Cannibus Crews Wall page.
